What is kill?

kill is used to terminate a running process gracefully. It sends a signal to the process and allows it to stop properly.

Example:

kill 1234
What is kill -9?

kill -9 forcefully terminates a process immediately without allowing it to clean up resources.

Example:

kill -9 1234
Interview Answer

kill gracefully stops a process, whereas kill -9 forcefully terminates a process when it is not responding.

Easy Way to Remember
kill     = Normal Stop
kill -9  = Force Stop
Real-Time Example

Suppose an application or script is stuck:

Check process:

ps -ef | grep python

Kill process:

kill 1234

If it doesn't stop:

kill -9 1234
Next Interview Question

What is a process?

A simple answer would be:

A process is a running instance of a program. Every running application in Linux has a unique Process ID (PID).

Example:

nginx
docker
java
python
bash

These are all processes when they are running.

✅ So remember:

Process = Running program
PID = Process ID
kill = Graceful stop
kill -9 = Force stop
